[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> Your task is to parallelize the serial graph construction and traversal algorithm and generate the same set of contigs as the serial version. The algorithm works with unique k-mers and their forward/backward extensions to construct a de Bruijn graph represented as a hash table with separate chaining.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> Reference: Georganas, E., Buluç, A., Chapman, J., Oliker, L., Rokhsar, D., & Yelick, K. (2014, November). Parallel de bruijn graph construction and traversal for de novo genome assembly. In SC'"'"'14: Proceedings of the International Conference for High Performance Computing, Networking, Storage and Analysis (pp. 437-448). IEEE.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> Input format: Each line contains KMER followed by tab and two characters representing left and right extensions (A/C/G/T/F where F means no extension).
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> Output format: Each output file should contain DNA contigs (sequences of A/C/G/T characters), one contig per line.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> Requirements:
[?2004l[?2004h> - Implement both serial and parallel UPC versions of the de Bruijn graph algorithm
[?2004l[?2004h> - A test input file named '"'"'test'"'"' is provided in the current directory (10,000 lines of k-mers)
[?2004l[?2004h> - Create a Makefile that builds both executables: '"'"'serial'"'"' (serial version) and '"'"'pgen'"'"' (parallel version)
[?2004l[?2004h> - Serial version must output contigs to '"'"'/app/serial.out'"'"'
[?2004l[?2004h> - Parallel version must output to files starting with '"'"'pgen'"'"' and ending with '"'"'.out'"'"' (e.g., /app/pgen_0.out, /app/pgen_1.out)
[?2004l[?2004h> - Verify correctness by ensuring parallel version generates identical contigs to /app/serial.out version (order may differ)
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> Implementation notes:
[?2004l[?2004h> - You will need to install Berkeley UPC compiler (download from https://upc.lbl.gov/download/release/berkeley_upc-2022.10.0.tar.gz)
[?2004l[?2004h> - Configure Berkeley UPC for SMP mode: ./configure --prefix=/usr/local --disable-mpi --enable-smp --disable-ibv --disable-shmem --disable-ofi --disable-ucx
[?2004l[?2004h> - When running pgen with pthreads, use: upcrun -n <num_threads> -shared-heap 256MB /app/pgen <input_file>
[?2004l[?2004h> - Due to the small dataset size, the parallel implementation is expected to be slower than the serial version due to UPC runtime overhead, thread synchronization, and communication costs
